Java follows strict OOP principles with class-based inheritance.
JavaScript is more flexible, using prototype-based inheritance and supporting OOP with ES6 classes.

While Java is a pure OOP language, JavaScript is multi-paradigm (supports OOP, functional, and procedural programming).

Feature	      Java (Class-based OOP)	              JavaScript (Prototype-based OOP)
Encapsulation	Uses access modifiers (privt, publi)	Uses closures or #private fields
Abstraction	  Uses abstract classes and interfaces	Uses private fields and closures
Inheritance	  Uses extends (class-based)	          Uses prototypes or extends (ES6)
Polymorphism	Method overloading and overriding	    Mostly method overriding
